item.title: • Project 0.11 • new forum!
item.dc:creator: @_CopyRight CopyRight
item.description:
@_CopyRight wrote:

“Virus Scans arent always acurate”

Recently, people have been flaming a certain indivdual just because their precious scanners detected something malicious about his source. The truth is, three staff members checked AND CLEARED that source. You people do not understand the following:
  1. Extracting an archive will not kill your computer
  2. Those programs cannot read java bytecode
  3. Those programs do not read ascii/utf-8 (whatever font your computer is using)
  4. Usually a scanner will go balistic over the following file types:

.exe (Win32 Executable)
.msi (Win64 Executable)
.bat (Win Command Line Batch file)
.com (Win Command Line file)
.cmd (Win Command Line file)

And a few more. Looking at that above list tells me personally that every source downloadable on this website will not come out clean. Here are precautions that you can take to make sure your computer stays safe:

  1. Do NOT download a file that you are unsure about. Have a staff member check it before downloading for security reasons.
  2. If someone sends you any link inside of a private message, DO NOT CLICK IT. It is a danger to your computer because it may contain a malicious-infected image or download.
  3. Do not download every single thing you see. Be careful on what you download. This means that you do not go out on http://google.com, search something, and then download it right away. Absolutely not! Always, always know what you are downloading.
  4. NEVER run something unless you are positive what is contained inside is safe.

Now, look at the following key points of this post and memorize them:

Follow the above rules when downloading any item, server, or client (this includes running that program)
Do not always believe your scanner. Scanners can always say something is infected even if it is as simple as a batch file
DO NOT EVER FLAME SOMEONE JUST BECAUSE IT SAYS INFECTED ON YOUR SCANNER
If you are uncomfortable about downloading a certain server or client, then do not download it or send a link to a staff member so that they can review it and see if it is clean

If you follow the points covered on this post, you can help make this community a better place to share files. Thank you.
